He made his professional debut for FC Zwolle before moving to VVV-Venlo and then Heerenveen, spending the second half of last season on loan at ADO Den Haag. He has appeared 10 times for Holland Under-21s.

Boro boss Aitor Karanka has now brought 10 players to Teesside this summer, including Chelsea striker Patrick Bamford who joined on a season-long loan on Friday.

